  "motivation": "The TextFormatUpdateEvent is fired when the formatting attributes of text content change within an EditContext. It provides a structured interface to access formatting information such as underline style, underline thickness, and other visual characteristics through the getTextFormats() method.\n\nCurrently, Chrome's implementation of underline style and thickness values in TextFormatUpdateEvent doesn't align with the Edit Context API specification. This misalignment can cause:\n1. Inconsistent rendering of underlines across different browsers.\n2. Difficulty in implementing cross-platform text editors that need to interpret underline styles.\n\nThe primary motivation is to enhance cross-browser consistency and provide developers with reliable, predictable formatting behavior that works identically across all compliant browsers.",
  "devtrial_instructions": null,
  "activation_risks": null,
  "measurement": null,
  "availability_expectation": null,
  "adoption_expectation": null,
